 9. Persistent Storage with Volumes :
    => Docker Compose helps you to manage persistent data using volumes.
    => Volumes are stored on the host machine and persist even if the container is stopped or removed.


Use Cases for Docker Compose
============================
 => Local Development Environment: Docker Compose is excellent for managing multi-container applications locally (e.g., a web app, a database, and a caching layer).
 => Microservices Architecture: If you're developing a system with multiple services that need to run together (e.g., front-end, back-end, database, message queue), Docker Compose allows you to manage them efficiently.
 => Automating Testing: You can use Docker Compose to set up a testing environment with the required services running, then tear it down when tests are done.
 => CI/CD Pipeline: Docker Compose can be integrated into your continuous integration/continuous deployment (CI/CD) pipeline to set up environments dynamically for testing and deployment.


